    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it’s just that \"rest\" feels temporary, you know? like waiting in a station between trains. but i don't think i want another train to come. i've seen enough. i've done the miles. it feels like there's this peace in just letting the journey end, instead of constantly trying to force the engine to keep running when it clearly wants to quit. does that even make sense, or am i just being dramatic?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
